import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='lat', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['lat'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['lat'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['lat'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['lat'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitudes in the U-District dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Latitude')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x="lat", y="key", data=data, ci=None, color='b')
    ax.axvline(x=data['lat'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean Latitude: {:.2f}'.format(data['lat'].mean()))
    ax.legend(loc='best')
    plt.xlabel('Latitude')
    plt.ylabel('Key')
    plt.title('What is the average latitude in the U-District dataset?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='key', kde=False, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['key'].isna().sum(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Missing Values')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("Are there any missing values in the 'key' field of the U-District dataset?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Key')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x=data['lat'], ax=ax, color='lightblue')
    ax.axvline(data['lat'].min(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Min: {data['lat'].min():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['lat'].max(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f"Max: {data['lat'].max():.2f}")
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title("What is the range of values in the 'lat' field of the U-District dataset?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Latitude')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
